			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">When you write to AOROM's port, you have to write <em>both</em> the desired 32K bank and the desired nametable selection, OR'd together. GNROM, Color Dreams, and <em>Holy Diver</em> are similar: you have to update PRG, CHR, and (in the case of <em>Holy Diver</em>) mirroring in every write. If you're not changing a given bitfield, you need to write the same value to that bitfield that you wrote last time, much as with the bitfields that make up PPU control registers $2000 and $2001.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
							</td>
						</tr>
						</table>
					</td>
				</tr>
				</table>
			</td>
		</tr>

